First off. Great discussion. I really appreciate the attention to detail and execution here.

My thoughts on a potential solution is to move away from the regex search and instead use a Python `list` or `set`. I also like the idea of an extendable or overridable setting of sensitive words to clean if found. This allows for **a)** whole word matching and **b)** customizable data cleaning depending on your usage.

The code snippet @bkovacev provided above is a great start here. One challenge I see will be case insensitive matching. This is what regex pattern search gives you almost for free. However, the pro's of extendability and not using regex I think is still worthwhile.
 
